    2. Create the Proxy Function

    Using Node.js with Express:

    const express = require('express');
const axios = require('axios');
require('dotenv').config();

const app = express();
app.use(express.json());

// Environment variables
const HEYGEN_API_KEY = process.env.HEYGEN_API_KEY;
const HEYGEN_BASE_URL = 'https://api.heygen.com';

// Middleware to verify requests
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  const apiKey = req.headers['x-proxy-api-key'];
  if (!apiKey || apiKey !== process.env.PROXY_API_KEY) {
    return res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });
  }
  next();
});

// Generic proxy endpoint
app.all('/:path(*)', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const { path } = req.params;
    const url = `${HEYGEN_BASE_URL}/${path}`;
    
    const response = await axios({
      method: req.method,
      url,
      data: req.method !== 'GET' ? req.body : undefined,
      params: req.method === 'GET' ? req.query : undefined,
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Api-Key': HEYGEN_API_KEY,
      },
    });
    
    res.status(response.status).json(response.data);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error proxying request:', error.message);
    res.status(error.response?.status || 500).json({
      error: true,
      message: error.message,
      details: error.response?.data
    });
  }
});

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Proxy server running on port ${PORT}`);
});

    Notification Setup Instructions

    1. Configure Email Notifications:

      • Go to your GitHub repository settings.

      • Navigate to the "Notifications" section.

      • Enable GitHub's built-in email notifications for repository owners.

      • Customize the notifications to include job summaries and run details as needed.

    2. Set Up Slack Webhook:

      • In your Slack workspace, create a new Incoming Webhook.

      • Copy the generated Slack webhook URL.

    3. Add Slack Webhook URL as GitHub Secret:

      • In your GitHub repository, go to "Settings" > "Secrets and variables" > "Actions".

      • Click "New repository secret".

      • Name the secret SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL.

      • Paste the Slack webhook URL and save.

    4. Customize Notification Messages in Workflow:

      • Use the GitHub Action slackapi/slack-github-action@v1.23.0 in your workflow YAML.

      • Reference the secret ${{ secrets.SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL }} for the webhook URL.

      • Configure the action inputs to customize the Slack message content.

      • For email notifications, rely on GitHubs built-in job summary and run details included in the emails.
